  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nCast\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (7e9e6a5 2022-08-22T00:04:53.96787182Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge cast call\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nI'm using an RPC endpoint with a self-signed certificate. I'm seeing the following error when I make the call: \"invalid peer certificate: UnknownIssuer\"\r\n\r\n I've placed the rootca into the following folders, but I'm not sure where cast reads trusted CAs from, or how to set a custom CA or client certificate for the command.\r\n* `/usr/local/share/ca-certificates/`\r\n* `/etc/ssl/certs/`",
